title: Bay Area Priority Development Areas and Growth Opportunity Areas (Copy)
name: Bay Area Priority Development Areas and Growth Opportunity Areas (Copy)
description: Geographies nominated by cities and counties as places to direct future population growth and public investment.  To qualify as a Priority Development Area, an area must be within an existing community, near transit with a maximum wait of 20 minutes at AM peak times, and planned for more housing.
